00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:55,100
The discipline in today's school

292
00:19:55,180 --> 00:19:56,080
is very strict.

293
00:19:57,620 --> 00:19:59,640
Quality-oriented education, after all.

294
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:01,000
Mom.

295
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:03,260
Dad.

296
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:05,640
I'll wash my feet myself.

297
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:06,940
I've grown up.

298
00:20:07,340 --> 00:20:08,780
You just need to study hard.

299
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:24,120
You are my superstar.

300
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:35,980
What's wrong with her?

301
00:20:36,920 --> 00:20:38,300
It's a girl thing.

302
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:39,800
Isn't she a boy?

303
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:40,800
SCREAMING GLASSES NOODLES

304
00:20:45,780 --> 00:20:47,700
Come downstairs for dinner.

305
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:48,980
Have you finished cooking?

306
00:20:49,220 --> 00:20:50,660
It's late.

307
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:51,440
I'm here.

308
00:20:51,440 --> 00:20:52,620
Dinner is ready.

309
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:54,680
I'm here.

310
00:20:54,680 --> 00:20:56,080
What did you make?

311
00:20:56,640 --> 00:20:57,640
Steamed pork.

312
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,020
Nice.

313
00:20:59,020 --> 00:20:59,620
Shrimps.

314
00:20:59,620 --> 00:21:00,480
This one is good.

315
00:21:00,480 --> 00:21:02,220
What about you, Liangliang?

316
00:21:02,220 --> 00:21:03,340
What's your dish?

317
00:21:03,340 --> 00:21:04,820
Fish.

318
00:21:06,340 --> 00:21:08,520
Thank you for spending so much.

319
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:13,520
Chopsticks.

320
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:14,820
- Come on. - Chopsticks.

321
00:21:14,820 --> 00:21:15,700
Water for children.

322
00:21:16,540 --> 00:21:17,800
Wine for adults.

323
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:18,920
Chopsticks.

324
00:21:18,920 --> 00:21:20,300
Here. Bowls.

325
00:21:20,980 --> 00:21:23,700
On the first day of school, we'll have dinner together.

326
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:24,860
It's a tradition.

327
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:27,640
But this year is different.

328
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:30,100
You're in the senior year.

329
00:21:30,740 --> 00:21:31,580
First,

330
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:34,800
wish you good luck in school.

331
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:36,220
Meanwhile,

332
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:38,700
I wish you could enter good universities.

333
00:21:38,820 --> 00:21:39,540
Okay.

334
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:46,320
Just let it be.

335
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:48,520
You three families can say that.

336
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:50,120
My brat son,

337
00:21:50,620 --> 00:21:51,700
perhaps can't.

338
00:21:51,700 --> 00:21:53,040
I told you not to call me that.

339
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:53,880
I want.

340
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:58,000
You two, knock it off.

341
00:21:58,760 --> 00:21:59,580
According to traditions,

342
00:22:00,240 --> 00:22:01,360
take a photo together.

343
00:22:01,360 --> 00:22:03,400
Yes.

344
00:22:10,460 --> 00:22:12,700
Cheese!

345
00:22:27,820 --> 00:22:29,340
I have two things to tell you.

346
00:22:30,600 --> 00:22:31,560
The first one.

347
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:34,060
There's a placement test this afternoon.

348
00:22:34,460 --> 00:22:36,600
You can find your weakness.

349
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:38,480
In the next year,

350
00:22:38,660 --> 00:22:40,140
you can focus on that.

351
00:22:41,020 --> 00:22:43,600
Another test?

352
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:44,720
The second one.

353
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:47,220
Our school will participate in the spring and summer

354
00:22:47,220 --> 00:22:50,060
mountain marathon team race organized by our city.

355
00:22:50,060 --> 00:22:51,100
The top three

356
00:22:51,100 --> 00:22:52,460
can gain extra points for NCEE.

357
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:53,980
Any volunteers?

358
00:22:56,940 --> 00:22:58,300
We're in senior year.

359
00:22:58,300 --> 00:23:00,580
Who wants any marathon race?

360
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:03,280
As there's no volunteer,

361
00:23:03,780 --> 00:23:04,820
I'll choose someone

362
00:23:04,820 --> 00:23:06,940
from the bottom of our class.

363
00:23:18,300 --> 00:23:19,420
Dear classmate,

364
00:23:19,520 --> 00:23:21,000
why did you reach your foot here?

365
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:22,760
Let me go.

366
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:25,020
Let me go.

367
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:30,000
Why do you reach your foot that far?

368
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:32,140
To kick the classmate in front of you?

369
00:23:36,580 --> 00:23:37,780
My foot is sore.

370
00:23:37,780 --> 00:23:40,100
I'm stretching...

371
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:54,720
Isn't this Ma Tian who wins Merit Student

372
00:23:54,720 --> 00:23:55,760
every year?

373
00:23:55,760 --> 00:23:56,520
Anything wrong?

374
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:58,220
You're also in the 16th exam room?

375
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:00,300
I'm a transfer student. I don't have grades here.

376
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:02,480
When the result comes out, I won't be here.

377
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:11,760
By the way,

378
00:24:11,980 --> 00:24:13,620
when the results come out,

379
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:15,300
you'll need to go for marathon.

380
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:16,860
Come on.

381
00:24:19,380 --> 00:24:20,840
So cocky.

382
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:21,700
Give me my pen.

383
00:24:21,840 --> 00:24:22,460
Okay.

384
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:23,820
I'll show him.

385
00:24:45,500 --> 00:24:46,100
Sir,

386
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:47,440
I've finished my paper.

387
00:24:47,900 --> 00:24:50,020
You can't hand it in now. Not until 30 minutes pass.

388
00:24:50,020 --> 00:24:51,000
Just sit for a while.

389
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:13,320
Do you have tissue?

390
00:25:13,320 --> 00:25:13,940
No.

391
00:25:13,940 --> 00:25:14,920
What's wrong?

392
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:18,100
I ate the noodles made by Jiao's shop.

393
00:25:18,100 --> 00:25:19,500
I got a bellyache.

394
00:25:20,140 --> 00:25:21,420
I ate it too.

395
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:27,960
We must be the marathon players.

396
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:29,280
Yes.

397
00:25:29,860 --> 00:25:30,940
I can't even figure out one question.

398
00:25:30,940 --> 00:25:32,620
I can't either. I'll be with you.

399
00:25:33,040 --> 00:25:34,860
Do you want another player?

400
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:51,160
That stinks.

401
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:52,860
He has loose bowels!

402
00:25:52,860 --> 00:25:54,000
My belly aches.

403
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:56,140
Loose bowels?

404
00:25:56,780 --> 00:25:58,900
Sir, I have a bellyache.

405
00:25:59,520 --> 00:26:00,700
Oh gosh. It stinks.

406
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:01,540
Lend some paper.

407
00:26:02,100 --> 00:26:04,080
That stinks.

408
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:13,600
What are you doing?

409
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:14,460
Open the gate!

410
00:26:14,460 --> 00:26:15,920
- What are you doing? - To pick my ball.

411
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:18,320
You said you develop in an all-round way.

412
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:19,120
Come and catch me!

413
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:21,140
You brat!

414
00:26:21,140 --> 00:26:22,500
How dare you cheat me?

415
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:24,740
Stop there!

416
00:26:25,900 --> 00:26:27,140
Stop there!

417
00:26:30,860 --> 00:26:32,200
I'm the top jock in school.

418
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,680
You want to catch me?

419
00:26:37,060 --> 00:26:39,520
Stop there!

420
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:43,940
Stop there!

421
00:26:50,700 --> 00:26:51,620
Justice citizens,

422
00:26:51,620 --> 00:26:53,400
help me catch that thief.

423
00:26:53,820 --> 00:26:54,680
Stop there!

424
00:26:55,720 --> 00:26:57,440
You brat, stop there!

425
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:59,400
If you dare, just keep running.

426
00:26:59,400 --> 00:27:01,220
I'd like to see where you're running.

427
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:08,620
Why did you tear my paper!

428
00:27:09,180 --> 00:27:10,540
Be polite, boy.

429
00:27:10,540 --> 00:27:11,820
You don't have grades now.

430
00:27:11,960 --> 00:27:12,860
Since now,

431
00:27:12,860 --> 00:27:14,420
we're players in the same team.

432
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:24,600
You son of a gun.

433
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:25,760
Get up!

434
00:27:26,800 --> 00:27:28,300
You're really good at running.

435
00:27:38,120 --> 00:27:39,160
Toy boy.

436
00:27:43,160 --> 00:27:45,180
I shouldn't cause troubles in the exam room.

437
00:27:45,520 --> 00:27:47,760
I shouldn't truant from school.

438
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:49,000
I shouldn't...

439
00:27:54,340 --> 00:27:56,140
I also shouldn't run out of school

440
00:27:56,140 --> 00:27:57,560
without permission.

441
00:27:57,900 --> 00:28:00,020
Every school wants their students

442
00:28:00,020 --> 00:28:02,420
to have an all-round development.

443
00:28:02,420 --> 00:28:03,780
I think this disciplinary case

444
00:28:03,780 --> 00:28:04,700
is a mirror.

445
00:28:04,700 --> 00:28:05,580
I'll also

446
00:28:05,940 --> 00:28:07,140
turn over a new leaf.

447
00:28:07,140 --> 00:28:09,140
Please supervise me!

448
00:28:12,460 --> 00:28:15,220
These two students are so rampant.

449
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:18,000
Nothing can be accomplished without norms or standards.

450
00:28:18,220 --> 00:28:20,880
They're the negative examples for you.

451
00:28:21,140 --> 00:28:21,740
Get down.

452
00:28:23,980 --> 00:28:26,500
Let's applaud to welcome

453
00:28:26,500 --> 00:28:29,480
Tu Jun and Ma Tian of senior year!

454
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:31,780
What's wrong?

455
00:28:31,820 --> 00:28:32,540
I have no idea.

456
00:28:35,620 --> 00:28:37,380
There have been many young heroes
from ancient times till now.

457
00:28:37,660 --> 00:28:39,460
These two students

458
00:28:39,460 --> 00:28:41,260
caught the thief last Friday,

459
00:28:41,300 --> 00:28:42,940
protecting the property of people

460
00:28:42,940 --> 00:28:45,320
and making the criminal get the punishment.

461
00:28:45,540 --> 00:28:48,260
They're our positive models.

462
00:28:48,260 --> 00:28:50,500
You should learn from them!

463
00:28:52,920 --> 00:28:53,540
Doggo!

464
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:04,940
Come, say something.

465
00:29:05,700 --> 00:29:07,260
At that time, we thought

466
00:29:07,340 --> 00:29:08,980
if we just ignored

467
00:29:08,980 --> 00:29:10,780
such a evil deed,

468
00:29:10,820 --> 00:29:11,700
then we'd fail

469
00:29:11,780 --> 00:29:13,540
the expectations of our school!

470
00:29:14,820 --> 00:29:15,540
So

471
00:29:15,700 --> 00:29:16,980
we looked at each other.

472
00:29:17,260 --> 00:29:18,580
And we decided

473
00:29:19,260 --> 00:29:20,100
whatever it took,

474
00:29:20,500 --> 00:29:22,340
we must catch that thief!

475
00:29:30,860 --> 00:29:32,020
What happened after you caught the thief?

476
00:29:33,300 --> 00:29:34,260
Then

477
00:29:34,500 --> 00:29:36,140
we sang a song.

478
00:29:37,100 --> 00:29:37,740
A song?

479
00:29:39,340 --> 00:29:40,080
Which song?

480
00:29:51,460 --> 00:29:55,020
Friends support each other for a lifetime.

481
00:29:55,060 --> 00:29:58,420
Those days passed forever.

482
00:29:58,500 --> 00:30:01,700
One sentence for a whole life.

483
00:30:01,900 --> 00:30:04,540
A lifetime relationship, a cup of...

484
00:30:05,020 --> 00:30:08,260
My friends, we're never alone.

485
00:30:08,300 --> 00:30:09,300
A word of...

486
00:30:09,900 --> 00:30:11,540
You'll understand.

487
00:30:11,540 --> 00:30:12,420
And...

488
00:30:13,420 --> 00:30:14,380
And...

489
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:19,500
And you, and me.

490
00:30:19,740 --> 00:30:20,940
Together!

491
00:30:20,980 --> 00:30:24,580
Friends support each other for a lifetime.

492
00:30:24,620 --> 00:30:27,980
Those days passed forever.

493
00:30:27,980 --> 00:30:31,140
One sentence for a whole life.

494
00:30:31,380 --> 00:30:35,200
A lifetime relationship, a cup of wine.

495
00:30:35,340 --> 00:30:38,460
Friends support each other for a lifetime.

496
00:30:38,620 --> 00:30:41,580
The one who succeeds first is the dog.

497
00:30:41,940 --> 00:30:43,500
And injuries.

498
00:30:43,700 --> 00:30:44,740
And pains.

499
00:30:44,740 --> 00:30:45,740
Ma Tian is so cool.

500
00:30:45,860 --> 00:30:47,020
And you.

501
00:30:47,020 --> 00:30:48,740
Hey, you belong to Teaty, okay?

502
00:30:49,060 --> 00:30:49,860
Go along.

503
00:30:50,420 --> 00:30:51,900
Those days passed forever.

504
00:30:51,940 --> 00:30:54,020
Isn't Doggo the cool one?

505
00:30:54,100 --> 00:30:57,660
And injuries, and pains.

506
00:30:57,940 --> 00:31:02,820
And you and me.

507
00:31:07,500 --> 00:31:09,240
I know clearly what happened.

508
00:31:09,580 --> 00:31:11,560
Why couldn't you control yourself?

509
00:31:12,060 --> 00:31:13,900
You just ran out of school.

510
00:31:14,500 --> 00:31:15,780
It's hard for me to handle it.

511
00:31:16,300 --> 00:31:18,700
What about I arrange another exam for you?

512
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:21,060
It doesn't matter. Forget it.

513
00:31:21,860 --> 00:31:23,540
It's not about the grades.

514
00:31:23,540 --> 00:31:24,880
It's the marathon.

515
00:31:25,140 --> 00:31:26,660
I've told everyone about the marathon.

516
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:29,300
I don't know how to explain it.

517
00:31:30,140 --> 00:31:31,880
It's okay, I'll do it.

518
00:31:32,700 --> 00:31:33,920
But I'll be the team lead.

519
00:31:35,420 --> 00:31:36,920
team lead is fine.

520
00:31:37,860 --> 00:31:39,440
You really wanna run?

521
00:31:41,740 --> 00:31:42,340
Or,

522
00:31:42,380 --> 00:31:43,500
you can go to another class.

523
00:31:43,860 --> 00:31:44,540
There are indeed

524
00:31:44,920 --> 00:31:46,340
some students always making trouble in the class.

525
00:31:46,860 --> 00:31:47,720
They may influence you.

526
00:31:51,180 --> 00:31:52,620
Are you blind!

527
00:31:55,940 --> 00:31:56,880
Nevermind.

528
00:31:57,620 --> 00:31:58,660
They won't influence me.

529
00:32:07,820 --> 00:32:09,020
Why does it rain suddenly?

530
00:32:09,320 --> 00:32:10,220
I have no idea.

531
00:32:11,460 --> 00:32:13,620
Sir, do you have any umbrellas?

532
00:32:13,860 --> 00:32:15,240
I'm sorry.

533
00:32:15,380 --> 00:32:16,940
It has been sold out.

534
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:18,080
Just sold out.

535
00:32:26,020 --> 00:32:27,020
Look at them.

536
00:32:27,500 --> 00:32:29,340
What on earth are they?

537
00:32:30,580 --> 00:32:33,220
They're more naughty than us.

538
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:37,480
These three boys are bad.

539
00:32:38,220 --> 00:32:40,820
One confessed in public, breaking school rules.

540
00:32:41,460 --> 00:32:44,080
One tore others' papers and did everything bad.

541
00:32:44,700 --> 00:32:46,880
Another one wrote a guide by himself,

542
00:32:47,220 --> 00:32:48,640
teaching others to pick up girls.

543
00:32:49,060 --> 00:32:51,380
It doesn't seem that he can find one.

544
00:32:51,780 --> 00:32:53,440
What do you think

545
00:32:53,620 --> 00:32:54,860
of the two newcomers?

546
00:32:54,860 --> 00:32:56,420
Just sanctimonious bad people.

547
00:32:56,420 --> 00:32:57,460
They're so petty.

548
00:32:57,740 --> 00:32:58,940
Students like them

549
00:32:58,940 --> 00:33:00,120
like reporting others secretly.

550
00:33:00,380 --> 00:33:01,100
Yes.

551
00:33:01,340 --> 00:33:02,460
They'll betray others

552
00:33:02,460 --> 00:33:03,860
to get higher grades.

553
00:33:04,600 --> 00:33:06,420
That one named Doggo

554
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:08,160
really tore your paper.

555
00:33:08,700 --> 00:33:10,180
It's the first time that I heard such a thing.

556
00:33:11,060 --> 00:33:12,520
Unbelievable.

557
00:33:13,260 --> 00:33:14,260
Naughty?

558
00:33:14,860 --> 00:33:17,420
Ma Tian doesn't look like a bad guy.

559
00:33:18,060 --> 00:33:19,020
Hercules Jiao,

560
00:33:19,380 --> 00:33:20,980
do you know bimbo effect?

561
00:33:20,980 --> 00:33:21,620
But why

562
00:33:21,620 --> 00:33:22,820
you also don't have brains?

563
00:33:25,900 --> 00:33:26,980
What do you mean?

564
00:33:27,300 --> 00:33:28,780
You mean I'm flat-chested.

565
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:30,120
So annoying.

566
00:33:31,340 --> 00:33:32,780
My umbrella is broken.

567
00:33:33,260 --> 00:33:33,860
Broken!

568
00:33:33,860 --> 00:33:35,440
Wait for me.

569
00:33:40,180 --> 00:33:41,500
What about that girl?

570
00:33:43,140 --> 00:33:44,260
I don't know.

571
00:33:50,740 --> 00:33:51,940
Right, what about Liu Wenqin?

572
00:33:57,440 --> 00:33:58,440
What?

573
00:33:59,700 --> 00:34:00,860
Still haven't found him.

574
00:34:03,300 --> 00:34:04,700
So we came here in vain?

575
00:34:05,700 --> 00:34:07,740
And we have classmates like them.

576
00:34:10,380 --> 00:34:11,500
What about we transfer back?

577
00:34:13,300 --> 00:34:14,300
We've already come here.

578
00:34:15,120 --> 00:34:16,440
I must find him.

579
00:34:22,540 --> 00:34:23,220
Jiaojiao,

580
00:34:23,880 --> 00:34:24,520
look at me.

581
00:34:29,120 --> 00:34:30,900
The list is about to be announced.

582
00:34:32,940 --> 00:34:34,500
I'm the top jock of school.

583
00:34:34,500 --> 00:34:35,180
You know that.

584
00:34:36,220 --> 00:34:37,940
Then you'll be the team lead.

585
00:34:37,940 --> 00:34:40,160
Then I'll be the team lead.

586
00:34:42,220 --> 00:34:43,900
Do you know what that means?

587
00:34:44,860 --> 00:34:45,740
Means what?

588
00:34:45,900 --> 00:34:47,300
It means

589
00:34:47,300 --> 00:34:48,980
I'll train you little toy boy

590
00:34:48,980 --> 00:34:51,259
to death.

591
00:34:52,140 --> 00:34:53,380
How do you do that?

592
00:34:57,700 --> 00:34:59,060
So hard.

593
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:08,420
Leapfrog with weight for three laps.

594
00:35:08,940 --> 00:35:09,540
That's a must.

595
00:35:09,620 --> 00:35:10,279
A must.

596
00:35:11,700 --> 00:35:13,339
Running up the stairs with weight

597
00:35:13,339 --> 00:35:15,020
and running uphill and downhill around our school.

598
00:35:15,060 --> 00:35:16,259
You must do it too.

599
00:35:16,299 --> 00:35:17,180
Yeah.

600
00:35:17,779 --> 00:35:18,580
Push-up and sit-up

601
00:35:18,580 --> 00:35:20,860
should be part of your daily life.

602
00:35:20,900 --> 00:35:21,860
Part of your daily life.

603
00:35:21,860 --> 00:35:22,520
Moreover,

604
00:35:23,140 --> 00:35:25,339
drink your tears of regret for offending me

605
00:35:25,339 --> 00:35:26,620
like water.

606
00:35:28,380 --> 00:35:31,380
That sounds intense and exciting.

607
00:35:32,660 --> 00:35:34,020
Are you scared?

608
00:35:34,020 --> 00:35:35,120
Don't be scared.

609
00:35:44,620 --> 00:35:45,660
I said

610
00:35:46,880 --> 00:35:48,980
students ranking the bottom

611
00:35:49,460 --> 00:35:51,020
should join the mountain marathon.

612
00:35:52,140 --> 00:35:53,260
What a coincidence.

613
00:35:53,260 --> 00:35:54,660
Most of them are in our Class One.

614
00:35:58,220 --> 00:35:59,140
Tu Jun.

615
00:35:59,140 --> 00:35:59,820
Here.

616
00:36:00,220 --> 00:36:01,380
Ding Rongliang.

617
00:36:01,420 --> 00:36:02,040
Here.

618
00:36:03,020 --> 00:36:04,140
Luo Shenxi,

619
00:36:07,340 --> 00:36:08,900
and Song Jie from Class Two.

620
00:36:11,540 --> 00:36:12,500
Ma Tian.

621
00:36:17,700 --> 00:36:18,820
You toy boy

622
00:36:18,860 --> 00:36:20,380
